\h Revelation
\toc1 Revelation
\toc2 Revelation
\toc3 Rev.
\mt2 Yohan's
\mt1 Revelation
\mt2 of Yeshua the messiah
\is1 Introduction
\ip \bk Yohan's (John's) revelation of Yeshua (Jesus) the messiah\bk* concerns events that will happen in the future. This was written long ago in a time when the believers were persecuted due to their faith in the master Yeshua, the messiah, and Yohan himself had been forcibly exiled to Patmos Island by the Roman authorities and held there. Yohan's main purpose for writing this was to give hope to the believers and to encourage them to persevere in their faith despite their persecution.
\ip A major portion of what's written in this document is the revelation by Yeshua the messiah to Yohan about incredible signs and all those symbols have a meaning and interpretation. At the time of writing, some were likely understood by the Christians of the time, but now, some of the symbols are very hard to interpret, and there's been a large range of interpretations from different people. But even though it's like that, there are also some signs that are easier to understand like вҖҳhornsвҖҷ which denote power and authority, and вҖҳswordвҖҷ which denotes war. The themes are repeated throughout this document in various different forms. But it's important to just understand the main points of what's written here: God will indeed destroy all of his enemies through the messiah Yeshua, and also, he will reward all his people who persevere in serving him, and then he'll bring them to live with him. The final major them concerns the new sky and earth that God will create, and concerning the new Yerushalem that will descend from heaven.
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 Introduction \ior 1:1-8\ior*
\io1 Yohan's first revelation in the form of a dream \ior 1:9-20\ior*
\io1 The letters sent to seven assemblies of believers \ior 2:1вҖ“3:22\ior*
\io1 The scroll with seven seals \ior 4:1вҖ“8:1\ior*
\io1 The seven trumpets \ior 8:2вҖ“11:19\ior*
\io1 The dinosaur and the two creatures \ior 12:1вҖ“13:18\ior*
\io1 The various revelations to Yohan as dreams \ior 14:1вҖ“15:8\ior*
\io1 The seven bowls of God's anger \ior 16:1-21\ior*
\io1 The destruction of Babylon and the defeat of all God's enemies \ior 17:1вҖ“20:10\ior*
\io1 The final judgement \ior 20:11-15\ior*
\io1 The new sky and earth, and the new Yerushalem \ior 21:1вҖ“22:5\ior*
\io1 Ending \ior 22:6-21\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\rem /s1 Introduction and Salutation; Prologue
\p
\v 1 \add This is\add* the revelationВҰ155327 thatВҰ155330 \nd GodВҰ155334\nd* gaveВҰ155331 to \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ155329\nd* to show to his slavesВҰ155338 \add to explain\add* what must happen soon. He communicated it by sending it via his messengerВҰ155350 to his slaveВҰ155354, Yohan
\v 2 who \add then\add* faithfully passed on everything he sawВҰ155371 of \nd God's\nd* messageВҰ155361 and the testimonyВҰ155366 of \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ155368\nd*.
\v 3 \add God will \add* bless anyone who reads or listens to the messagesВҰ155380 of this prophecyВҰ155384 and obeys what's writtenВҰ155390 in itВҰ155389, becauseВҰ155392 the timeВҰ155393 \add of these events happening\add* is close.
\s1 The greetings to seven assemblies of believers
\rem /s1 Christ's messages to seven churches; John's Greeting to the Seven Churches; Greetings to the Seven Churches; Greetings and doxology
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 1:4: a \xt Exo 3:14; \xo b \xt Rev 4:5.\x*\add This letter is from\add* Yohan to the seven assembliesВҰ155398 in AsiaВҰ155402 \add Minor\add*:
\p Grace and peaceВҰ155406 to you all from the \add God\add* who is and was and will be, and from the seven spiritsВҰ155422 who are in front of hisВҰ155429 throneВҰ155428,
\v 5 \x + \xo 1:5: a \xt Isa 55:4; \xo b \xt Psa 89:27.\x*and from Yeshua \add the\add* \nd messiahВҰ155433\nd*, the faithfulВҰ155437 witnessВҰ155435, the firstВҰ155439 to come back to life, and the rulerВҰ155445 of all the leaders \add of the nations\add* of the world.
\p \add Yeshua \add* loves us and he has releasedВҰ155456 us from ourВҰ155463 sinsВҰ155462 by hisВҰ155467 bloodВҰ155466,
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6: \xt Exo 19:6; Rev 5:10.\x*and made us into a kingdomВҰ155473 of priestsВҰ155476 to \nd GodВҰ155479\nd* hisВҰ155483 fatherВҰ155482, and he is deserving of honour and power throughout the ages. MayВҰ155501 itВҰ155501 beВҰ155501 soВҰ155501.
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 1:7: a \xt Dan 7:13; Mat 24:30; Mrk 13:26; Luk 21:27; 1Th 4:17; \xo b \xt Zech 12:10; Yhn 19:34,37; \xo c \xt Zech 12:10; Mat 24:30.\x*LookВҰ155502, he's going to come \add back\add* in the cloudsВҰ155507, and everyoneВҰ155513 will see himвҖ”the one who they spearedвҖ”and all the tribesВҰ155525 on the earthВҰ155527 will be mourningВҰ155520 over him. REWORK OT QUOTES
\p
\v 8 \x + \xo 1:8: a \xt Rev 22:13; \xo b \xt Exo 3:14.\x*вҖңI am the A and the Z,вҖқ says \nd YahwehВҰ155544 GodВҰ155546\nd*, the one who is and was and will beвҖ”the most powerful one.
\s1 Yohan sees the messiah
\rem /s1 Vision of the Son of Man; A Vision of Christ; One like a Son of Man
\p
\v 9 I, Yohan, am yourВҰ155562 brotherВҰ155561 and partner in the suffering \add that's typical of those who follow\add* Yeshua. \add I've been exiled to\add* PatmosВҰ155588 Island where I endureВҰ155574 becauseВҰ155589 I believe God's messageВҰ155592 and \nd Yeshua's\nd* testimonyВҰ155598 and \add look forward to\add* his kingdomВҰ155572.
\v 10 One Sunday \add while I was meditating\add*, \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ155604\nd* gave me a vision, andВҰ155609 I heardВҰ155610 a voiceВҰ155614 behindВҰ155612 me that seemed as loudВҰ155615 as a trumpetВҰ155619 blast
\v 11 that said, вҖңWrite down what youВҰ155635 see \add here\add* on a scrollВҰ155640 and sendВҰ155642 it to the sevenВҰ155644 assembliesВҰ155645 \add of believers\add*вҖ”to \add the cities of\add* EphesusВҰ155650, SmyrnaВҰ155653, PergamumВҰ155656, ThyatiraВҰ155659, SardisВҰ155666, PhiladelphiaВҰ155669, and to LaodiceaВҰ155672.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ155673 I turned to see who was talkingВҰ155680 to me, andВҰ155673 I sawВҰ155687 sevenВҰ155688 goldenВҰ155690 lamp holders,
\v 13 and standing among them was a man who looked like humanity's child,\f + \fr 1:13 \ft It's not certain what was meant here: either вҖҳa man who looked like humanity's childвҖҷ or вҖҳa form that looked like a human manвҖҷ.\f* wearing a long robe with a goldenВҰ155711 sash around HisВҰ155702 chest.\x + \xo 1:13: a \xt Dan 7:13; \xo b \xt Dan 10:5.\x*
\v 14 HisВҰ155716 hairВҰ155719 was gleaming white like wool or snow andВҰ155714 hisВҰ155716 eyesВҰ155729 were \add bright\add* like a fiery flameВҰ155732.\x + \xo 1:14: \xt Dan 7:9.\x*
\v 15 HisВҰ155737 feetВҰ155736 shone like bronzeВҰ155739 that had been refinedВҰ155743 in a furnaceВҰ155742, and hisВҰ155737 voice was like the sound of a \add river of rushing\add* waterВҰ155752.\x + \xo 1:15: \xt Eze 1:24; 43:2.\x*
\v 16 He was holdingВҰ155755 sevenВҰ155764 starsВҰ155763 in his rightВҰ155759 handВҰ155761 and a sharpВҰ155772 swordВҰ155770 was extending from his mouthВҰ155768, and his faceВҰ155776 was like the sunВҰ155781 shiningВҰ155782 at itsВҰ155786 brightest.
\v 17 And when I sawВҰ155789 him, I quickly lay at his feetВҰ155795, \add breathless\add* like a deadВҰ155799 man, butВҰ155787 he placed his rightВҰ155804 handВҰ155804 on me, and told me, вҖңDon't be afraid. \em I am\em* the firstВҰ155817 and the last.\x + \xo 1:17: \xt Isa 44:6; 48:12; Rev 2:8; 22:13.\x*
\v 18 I lived and died \add here on the earth\add*, butВҰ155821 look, \add now\add* I'm alive \add again\add* and will live for all eternity, and I control the keys over deathВҰ155842 and over hell.
\v 19 SoВҰ155849 record what you're seeing \add now\add* as well as \add what I'll show you\add* about current and future events.
\v 20 This is the meaning of the seven stars thatВҰ155870 you saw in myВҰ155878 rightВҰ155876 handВҰ155876 and of the seven goldenВҰ155884 lamp holders:\x + \xo 1:20: \xt 1:12.\x* The seven stars represent \add God's\add* messengersВҰ155888 \add watching over\add* those seven groups of believers,\x + \xo 1:20: \xt 1:11.\x* and the seven lamp holders represent those groups of believers.
\c 2
\s1 The message to the assembly in Ephesus
\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Ephesus
\p
\v 1 To the assembly'sВҰ155914 messengerВҰ155908 in EphesusВҰ155912 writeВҰ155915:
\p The one holding the seven starsВҰ155922 in hisВҰ155926 rightВҰ155925 handВҰ155925, the one walkingВҰ155929 among the seven goldenВҰ155936 lampstandsВҰ155934, says these \add things\add*:
\v 2 вҖңI know about your activities and work, and your enduranceВҰ155947 and that you can'tВҰ155951 tolerate evilВҰ155954 people, and that you've investigated the ones who call themselvesВҰ155961 missionaries butВҰ155941 are not, and you've foundВҰ155969 them to be frauds.
\v 3 \add I'm aware that\add* you've enduredВҰ155975 and even suffered \add persecution\add* becauseВҰ155982 you've \add believed in\add* me, butВҰ155974 you've never given up.
\v 4 However, I do have something againstВҰ155994 you: you've abandoned the loveВҰ155998 that you firstВҰ156001 had.
\v 5 SoВҰ156019 \add now, you need to\add* rememberВҰ156006 whereВҰ156008 you'veВҰ156009 fallenВҰ156009 from, and repent and repeat how you behaved at the beginning, butВҰ156019 if you don't, I'll come to you and if you don't repent, I'll removeВҰ156026 yourВҰ156029 lampstandВҰ156028 from itsВҰ156033 placeВҰ156032.
\v 6 But you do have this going for you: you hate what the \add disciples of\add* Nicolaus are doing,\f + \fr 2:7 \ft Nicolaus' disciples ate food that had been sacrificed to idols and committed sexual sins.\f* just like I do.
\p
\v 7 Everyone who wantsВҰ156051 to understandВҰ156051 needsВҰ156053 to listenВҰ156053 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ156056\nd* is sayingВҰ156057 to the assembliesВҰ156060.
\p I will grant \add the right\add* to eatВҰ156067 from the treeВҰ156070 \add thatВҰ156073 gives\add* lifeВҰ156072 in God's paradiseВҰ156079 to everyone who overcomesВҰ156064.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:7: a \xt Gen 2:9; Rev 22:2; \xo b \xt Eze 28:13; 31:8 (LXX).\x*
\s1 The message to the assembly in Smyrna
\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Smyrna
\p
\v 8 To the assembly'sВҰ156092 messengerВҰ156086 in SmyrnaВҰ156090 writeВҰ156094:\x + \xo 2:8: \xt Isa 44:6; 48:12; Rev 1:17; 22:13.\x*
\p The one who's the firstВҰ156099 andВҰ156084 the last, who died butВҰ156084 livedВҰ156107 \add again\add*, says these things:
\v 9 вҖңI know about your suffering and your povertyВҰ156117, but you'reВҰ156121 \add actually\add* rich! I also know how about the slanderВҰ156124 of those who consider themselvesВҰ156132 to be Jews, but they're not \add true\add* Jews because \add вүҲtheir master is\add* SatanВҰ156139.
\v 10 Don't be afraid about what you'reВҰ156144 going to sufferВҰ156146. Yes, the devilВҰ156153 will throwВҰ156150 some of you into prisonВҰ156159 where yourВҰ156154 \add faith\add* will be testedВҰ156161, and you'll experience persecution for ten daysВҰ156167. \add Just\add* remain faithful, even if it means deathВҰ156172, and I'llВҰ156174 give you lifeВҰ156179 as a reward.
\p
\v 11 Everyone who wantsВҰ156181 to understandВҰ156181 needsВҰ156183 to listenВҰ156183 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ156186\nd* is sayingВҰ156187 to the assembliesВҰ156189.
\p Anyone who \add stays true\add* won'tВҰ156193 be affected by the secondВҰ156199 deathВҰ156197.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:11: \xt Rev 20:14; 21:8.\x*
\s1 The message to the assembly in Pergamum
\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Pergamum
\p
\v 12 To the assembly'sВҰ156206 messengerВҰ156202 in PergamumВҰ156205 writeВҰ156207:
\p The one with the sharpВҰ156217 swordВҰ156213 says these things:
\v 13 вҖңI know where you live: where Satan's throneВҰ156227 is. Despite that, you firmly \add believe in me\add* and you haven't denied your faithВҰ156240 in me, even when AntipasВҰ156249, the faithful \add man who told others about me\add* was killedВҰ156257 in your \add city\add*, where Satan lives.
\v 14 ButВҰ156296 I do have a few things againstВҰ156267 you: you have some people thereВҰ156273 who hold to \add the ancient prophet\add* Balaam's teaching.\x + \xo 2:14: a \xt Num 22:5,7; 31:16; Deu 23:4; \xo b \xt Num 25:1-3.\x* He taughtВҰ156276 \add Moab's king\add*, BalakВҰ156284, how to temptВҰ156288 the Israelis and to eat \add food\add* that had been sacrificedВҰ156295 to idols, and to be sexuallyВҰ156297 immoralВҰ156297.
\v 15 In the same way, some of youВҰ156301 also follow the teachingsВҰ156304 of Nicolaus' disciples.\f + \fr 2:15 \ft They eat food that has been sacrificed to idols, and they commit sexual sins.\f*
\v 16 SoВҰ156313 turn away from all that, otherwise I'llВҰ156320 come soon andВҰ156319 battle against them with the word of myВҰ156328 mouthВҰ156327.
\p
\v 17 EveryoneВҰ156363 who wantsВҰ156330 to understandВҰ156330 needsВҰ156332 to listenВҰ156332 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ156335\nd* is sayingВҰ156336 to the assembliesВҰ156338.
\p AnyoneВҰ156363 who \add stays true\add* will be given hiddenВҰ156349 food from heaven, and I'llВҰ156341 give \add each of\add* them a whiteВҰ156354 stone with a new nameВҰ156359 writtenВҰ156361 on it thatВҰ156348 no one knows apart from the person receivingВҰ156369 it.вҖқ\x + \xo 2:17: a \xt Exo 16:14-15; 16:33-34; Yhn 6:48-50; \xo b \xt Isa 62:2; 65:15.\x*
\s1 The message to the assembly in Thyatira
\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Thyatira
\p
\v 18 To the assembly'sВҰ156377 messengerВҰ156372 in ThyatiraВҰ156376 writeВҰ156378:
\p God's son, the one with eyesВҰ156388 like a flameВҰ156391 of fireВҰ156393 andВҰ156394 with feetВҰ156396 like bronzeВҰ156399, says:
\v 19 вҖңI know what you've been doing, and \add about\add* your loveВҰ156406 and faithВҰ156409, and your serviceВҰ156413 and enduranceВҰ156417, and what you're doing now is better than what you firstВҰ156428 did.
\v 20 ButВҰ156453 I have againstВҰ156431 you that you tolerate that woman JezebelВҰ156442 who calls herselfВҰ156448 a prophetessВҰ156451, and she deceives my servants by teachingВҰ156454 them to be sexuallyВҰ156462 immoralВҰ156462 and to eat \add food that's been\add* offered to idols.\x + \xo 2:20: \xt 1Ki 16:31; 2Ki 9:22,30.\x*
\v 21 Even though I've given her timeВҰ156470 to repent, she's \add still\add* not willing to turn away from her immoralityВҰ156480.
\v 22 Listen, I'm going to \add punish her with a terrible sickness\add*, and to punish those who are committingВҰ156496 adulteryВҰ156496 with her with terrible suffering if they don'tВҰ156503 turn away from what she's doing.
\v 23 I will kill herВҰ156514 childrenВҰ156513, thenВҰ156511 all the assembliesВҰ156522 will know that I am the one who searchesВҰ156527 \add people's\add* affections and heartsВҰ156530, and who \add punishes or rewards\add* each one of you depending on yourВҰ156538 actions.\x + \xo 2:23: a \xt Psa 7:9; Jer 17:10; \xo b \xt Psa 62:12.\x*
\p
\v 24 But the rest of you \add believers in the city\add* of ThyatiraВҰ156548 haven't obeyed that woman's teachingsВҰ156553 and haven't taken part in what she calls вҖҳthe secret practices that SatanВҰ156563 taughtВҰ156553 herвҖҷ, I have something to say to you all as well. I won'tВҰ156550 give you any other other burdenВҰ156572
\v 25 except just to continue to obey the true teaching thatВҰ156579 you've received, untilВҰ156578 I return.
\v 26 And anyone who's victorious, who continues to do what I command untilВҰ156588 the endВҰ156589, I'llВҰ156593 give them authorityВҰ156595 to rule over the people groups on earth.\x + \xo 2:26-27: \xt Psa 2:8-9 (LXX).\x*
\v 27 They'll rule them with irresistible power, andВҰ156599 \add those who rebel\add* will be smashed like \add unwanted\add* clay pots,
\v 28 just like \add the authority\add* that I'veВҰ156614 receivedВҰ156615 from myВҰ156619 fatherВҰ156618. And I'llВҰ156621 give them the morningВҰ156626 starВҰ156624.
\p
\v 29 Everyone who wantsВҰ156628 to understandВҰ156628 needsВҰ156630 to listenВҰ156630 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ156633\nd* is sayingВҰ156634 to the assembliesВҰ156636.вҖқ
\c 3
