\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Sardis
\p
\v 1 To the assembly'sВҰ156643 messengerВҰ156639 in SardisВҰ156642 writeВҰ156645:
\p The one having the seven spiritsВҰ156652 of \nd GodВҰ156654\nd* and the seven starsВҰ156658 says these things: вҖңI know what you're achieving and that you have a reputationВҰ156665 of being вҖҳaliveвҖҷ, butВҰ156637 you're \add actually\add* deadВҰ156670.
\v 2 So wake up \add from the dead\add* and strengthenВҰ156675 what's left and was about to dieВҰ156683, becauseВҰ156685 yourВҰ156687 actions have been inadequate in God's sight.
\v 3 Remember how you \add first\add* listened to and internalised \add God's message\add*, and how you obeyed it and repentedВҰ156704. If you don'tВҰ156708 wake up \add soon\add*, I'll come \add unexpectedly\add*вҖ”you'll certainly not know \add in advance\add* when I'll be coming.\x + \xo 3:3: \xt Mat 24:43-44; Luk 12:39-40; Rev 16:15.\x*
\v 4 ButВҰ156742 youВҰ156728 do have a few people in SardisВҰ156734 who haven't stained theirВҰ156741 records, and becauseВҰ156750 they are worthyВҰ156751, they'll \add be\add* dressed in whiteВҰ156749 and walkВҰ156743 with me.
\v 5 \add So\add* anyone who conquers will be dressed like that in \add pure\add* whiteВҰ156761, and I certainly won'tВҰ156764 erase their names from the Book of Life, butВҰ156762 I'llВҰ156765 declare their names to myВҰ156784 fatherВҰ156783 and to hisВҰ156768 messengersВҰ156788.\x + \xo 3:5: a \xt Exo 32:32-33; Psa 69:28; Rev 20:12; \xo b \xt Mat 10:32; Luk 12:8.\x*
\p
\v 6 Everyone who wantsВҰ156791 to understandВҰ156791 needsВҰ156793 to listenВҰ156793 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ156796\nd* is sayingВҰ156797 to the assembliesВҰ156799.вҖқ
\s1 The message to the assembly in Filadelfia
\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Philadelphia
\p
\v 7 To the assembly'sВҰ156807 messengerВҰ156802 in FiladelfiaВҰ156805 writeВҰ156809:\x + \xo 3:7: \xt Isa 22:22; Yob 12:14.\x*
\p The holy one, the true one, the one havingВҰ156819 \add King\add* David's key \add to the city\add*, the one who opens \add doors\add* no one can shut, andВҰ156800 who shuts \add doors\add* no one can open, says:
\v 8 вҖңI know \add everything\add* you've been doing. ListenВҰ156850, I have placed an openedВҰ156855 doorВҰ156854 in front of you thatВҰ156856 no one can shut. You aren'tВҰ156874 very strong, yet you've obeyed myВҰ156870 instructions and you haven't disownedВҰ156875 knowingВҰ156845 me.
\v 9 ListenВҰ156879, I'll give thoseВҰ156882 \add people\add* from Satan'sВҰ156887 synagogueВҰ156885 (the ones who say that they're \add believing\add* Jews, butВҰ156893 they're notвҖ”they're lyingВҰ156897), I'll make them so that they will come and bow down in front of you, and \add then\add* they'll knowВҰ156912 that I love you.\x + \xo 3:9: a \xt Isa 49:23; 60:14; \xo b \xt Isa 43:4.\x*
\v 10 BecauseВҰ156919 you followed myВҰ156926 instructions about persevering, I will spare you from the time of trouble thatВҰ156935 all of humanity will soon experience (whichВҰ156935 will test everyone livingВҰ156945 on the earthВҰ156948).
\v 11 I'll come quicklyВҰ156951. Hold firmly to what you have so that no one can takeВҰ156957 away yourВҰ156960 crownВҰ156959.
\v 12 Anyone who's an overcomerВҰ156962, I'llВҰ156963 make them a pillarВҰ156966 in my god's templeВҰ156969 and they'll never leave it again. I will write my god's name on them, and the name of my god's cityВҰ156993 (the new Jerusalem which will come down out of heavenВҰ157005 from my god), and my new name.\x + \xo 3:12: a \xt Rev 21:2; \xo b \xt Isa 62:2; 65:15.\x*
\p
\v 13 Everyone who wantsВҰ157017 to understandВҰ157017 needsВҰ157019 to listenВҰ157019 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ157022\nd* is sayingВҰ157023 to the assembliesВҰ157025.вҖқ
\s1 The message to the assembly in Laodicea
\rem /s1 The Message to the Church in Laodicea
\p
\v 14 To the assembly'sВҰ157032 messengerВҰ157028 in LaodiceaВҰ157031 writeВҰ157034:\x + \xo 3:14: \xt Prv 8:22.\x*
\p The truth, the faithfulВҰ157043 andВҰ157044 true witnessВҰ157041, the originator of God's creationВҰ157052, says:
\v 15 вҖңI'm aware of what you've been doing \add and\add* that you'reВҰ157062 neitherВҰ157060 hot nor cold. (You'd benefit\f + \fr 3:15 \ft TC: Some manuscripts don't have this parenthesised sentence at all, and some later manuscripts have вҖҳI wishвҖҷ instead of вҖҳYou'd benefitвҖҷ.\f* if you were hot or cold.)
\v 16 So becauseВҰ157073 you'reВҰ157076 lukewarmВҰ157075, neitherВҰ157078 hot nor coldВҰ157083, I'll spit you out of myВҰ157094 mouthВҰ157092.
\v 17 You brag, вҖҳI'm rich, \add yes\add* I'veВҰ157101 grown rich and don't have any needs,вҖҷ butВҰ157100 you don't realise that you'reВҰ157096 \add actually\add* miserableВҰ157114 and pitiable, and poor and blindВҰ157122 and nakedВҰ157124.
\v 18 I advise you to buy goldВҰ157131 from me that's been refinedВҰ157132 by fireВҰ157134 so that you might get rich, and buy whiteВҰ157139 clothesВҰ157138 so that you can dress yourselfВҰ157141 so that the shameВҰ157146 of your nakednessВҰ157148 might not be displayed, and buy ointment to rub on your eyesВҰ157157 so that you'll be able to see.
\v 19 I tell off and disciplineВҰ157168 those that I love, so be earnest and turn away from your disobedience.\x + \xo 3:19: \xt Prv 3:12; Heb 12:6.\x*
\v 20 Yes, I stand at the door and knockВҰ157180вҖ”if anyoneВҰ157182 hears myВҰ157186 voiceВҰ157185 and opens the door, I will come in and eat with him, and he'll eat with me.
\v 21 Anyone who overcomesВҰ157205, I'llВҰ157206 give the right to sit with me on my throne, just like when I conquered and sat with my fatherВҰ157223 on hisВҰ157228 throne.
\p
\v 22 Everyone who wantsВҰ157230 to understandВҰ157230 needsВҰ157232 to listenВҰ157232 to what \add God's\add* \nd spiritВҰ157235\nd* is sayingВҰ157236 to the assembliesВҰ157238.
\c 4
\s1 Worshipping in heaven
\rem /s1 Visions of heaven; Worship in Heaven; The Heavenly Worship; The Throne in Heaven
\p
\v 1 AfterВҰ157239 that, I lookedВҰ157241 and wowВҰ157243, a doorВҰ157244 opening in heavenВҰ157248, and the firstВҰ157254 voiceВҰ157252 that I'd heardВҰ157256 that sounded like a trumpetВҰ157258 told me, вҖңCome up here and I'llВҰ157268 show you what mustВҰ157268 happen afterВҰ157274 those things.вҖқ
\v 2 ImmediatelyВҰ157277 I was in the \nd spiritВҰ157280\nd* and wowВҰ157282, a throne was appearing in heavenВҰ157287 with someone sittingВҰ157295 on it.\x + \xo 4:2-3: \xt Eze 1:26-28; 10:1.\x*
\v 3 The one sittingВҰ157299 there \add sparkled like jewels\add*, and an emerald-looking rainbowВҰ157313 encircled the throneВҰ157316.
\v 4 Surrounding that throne were twenty-four other thrones, and on them sat twenty-four eldersВҰ157342 dressed in whiteВҰ157347 and with goldenВҰ157355 crownsВҰ157354 on theirВҰ157353 headsВҰ157352.
\v 5 From the \add centre\add* throne came lightningВҰ157361 flashes and thunderousВҰ157366 sounds and voicesВҰ157364. In front of it, seven torches were burningВҰ157371, whichВҰ157378 are God's seven spiritsВҰ157383.\x + \xo 4:5: a \xt Exo 19:16; Rev 8:5; 11:19; 16:18; \xo b \xt Eze 1:13; \xo c \xt Rev 1:4; Zech 4:2.\x*
\v 6 In front of the throne was somethingВҰ157386 like a seaВҰ157391 of glassВҰ157392 that was as clear as crystalВҰ157394.
\p Around the throne were four livingВҰ157405 creaturesВҰ157405, covered \add both\add* front andВҰ157395 back with eyesВҰ157407.\x + \xo 4:6: \xt Eze 1:22.\x*
\v 7 This firstВҰ157415 living creature resembled a lionВҰ157417, the secondВҰ157420 resembled a bull, the thirdВҰ157426 had a faceВҰ157431 like a man, andВҰ157411 the fourthВҰ157439 one resembled a flyingВҰ157443 eagleВҰ157442.
\v 8 Each of the fourВҰ157446 livingВҰ157447 creaturesВҰ157447 had sixВҰ157459 wingsВҰ157458 with eyesВҰ157465 all aroundВҰ157460 and underneath them. Day and nightВҰ157472 they never stop sayingВҰ157473:\x + \xo 4:8: a \xt Eze 1:18; 10:12; \xo b \xt Isa 6:2-3.\x*
\q1 вҖҳHoly, holy, holy,
\q2 is \nd YahwehВҰ157483\nd*, almightyВҰ157487 \nd GodВҰ157485\nd*,
\q1 who was and is and is to come.вҖҷ
\p
\v 9 Whenever the living creaturesВҰ157501 praise the one sittingВҰ157509 on the throneВҰ157514 and honourВҰ157504 him and thankВҰ157506 him (the one who lives through all the ages),
\v 10 the twenty-four eldersВҰ157529 drop to their knees with their faces to the ground in front of the one sittingВҰ157532 on the throne and worship the one who lives through all the ages. They place their crownsВҰ157551 down in front of the throne and say:
\q1
\v 11 вҖңYou, ourВҰ157565 \nd GodВҰ157564\nd* and \nd masterВҰ157561\nd*, are worthy to receiveВҰ157568 praise and honourВҰ157573 and powerВҰ157576,
\q2 becauseВҰ157577 you created everything.
\q1 Everything exists just as you determined to create it.вҖқ
\c 5
\s1 The scroll and the lamb
\rem /s1 The Lamb Opens the Scroll; The Scroll and the Lamb
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ157592 I sawВҰ157593 a scrollВҰ157603 in the right-hand of the one sittingВҰ157599 on the throneВҰ157602. It had writing on both sides, andВҰ157592 had been sealedВҰ157610 with sevenВҰ157612 \add wax\add* sealsВҰ157611.\x + \xo 5:1: \xt Eze 2:9-10; Isa 29:11.\x*
\v 2 I also sawВҰ157614 a powerful messengerВҰ157615 who was asking in a loudВҰ157621 voiceВҰ157620, вҖңWho's worthyВҰ157624 to breakВҰ157630 the sealsВҰ157632 andВҰ157629 open the scrollВҰ157628?вҖқ
\v 3 ButВҰ157634 there wasn't any person on earth or \add in the place of the dead\add* who was permitted to open the scrollВҰ157653 andВҰ157642 read itВҰ157657.
\v 4 I began to cry loudly, becauseВҰ157662 no one could be foundВҰ157666 who was worthyВҰ157664 to open the scrollВҰ157671 or look inside itВҰ157674.
\v 5 ThenВҰ157675 one of the eldersВҰ157679 said to me, вҖңStop crying. LookВҰ157684, here's the lionВҰ157687 from the tribeВҰ157692 of YudahВҰ157693. He's the descendant of \add King\add* DavidВҰ157696 who's a conqueror \add who's competent\add* to break the sealsВҰ157706 andВҰ157702 open the scrollВҰ157701.вҖқ\x + \xo 5:5: a \xt Gen 49:9; \xo b \xt Isa 11:1,10.\x*
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ157711 I sawВҰ157712 a lamb standing there between the throneВҰ157717 and the fourВҰ157720 livingВҰ157721 creaturesВҰ157721 and the eldersВҰ157726. The lamb looked like it had been slaughtered, and it had seven hornsВҰ157734 and seven eyesВҰ157737 whichВҰ157739 are God's seven spiritsВҰ157744 thatВҰ157739 had been sentВҰ157751 throughout the world.\x + \xo 5:6: a \xt Isa 53:7; \xo b \xt Zech 4:10.\x*
\v 7 The lamb wentВҰ157757 up to the throne andВҰ157756 accepted \add the scroll\add* from the rightВҰ157764 handВҰ157764 of the one sittingВҰ157767 on the throne.
\v 8 WhenВҰ157771 he'd taken the scrollВҰ157775, the four livingВҰ157778 creaturesВҰ157778 and the twenty-four elders knelt down in front of the lambВҰ157787. Each elder held a harp and a bowl thatВҰ157798 was full of incenseВҰ157797 (whichВҰ157798 symbolised the prayersВҰ157802 of the believers).\x + \xo 5:8: \xt Psa 141:2.\x*
\v 9 They sung a new song \add like this\add*:\x + \xo 5:9: \xt Psa 33:3; 98:1; Isa 42:10.\x*
\q1 вҖңIt's you who's worthy to take the scrollВҰ157815 and break itsВҰ157820 sealsВҰ157819,
\q1 becauseВҰ157821 you were slaughtered and with yourВҰ157831 bloodВҰ157830 you purchased \add people\add* for \nd GodВҰ157826\nd*
\q2 from everyВҰ157833 tribeВҰ157834 and language and people group and nationВҰ157840.
\q1
\v 10 You've made them to be a kingdomВҰ157848\x + \xo 5:10: \xt Exo 19:6; Rev 1:6.\x*
\q2 and to be priestsВҰ157852 to \add serve\add* ourВҰ157847 \nd GodВҰ157846\nd*,
\q2 and theyВҰ157855 will reignВҰ157855 on the earthВҰ157859.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ157860 I lookedВҰ157861 and I heardВҰ157863 the voicesВҰ157865 of the livingВҰ157874 creaturesВҰ157874 and eldersВҰ157877 that were aroundВҰ157869 the throneВҰ157871 along with millions of \add God's\add* messengersВҰ157866\x + \xo 5:11: \xt Dan 7:10.\x*
\v 12 sayingВҰ157888 with loudВҰ157890 voicesВҰ157889:
\q1 вҖңThe lambВҰ157895 thatВҰ157896 was slaughtered is worthy to receiveВҰ157898 powerВҰ157900 and richesВҰ157903,
\q1 and wisdomВҰ157905 and strengthВҰ157907 and honourВҰ157909 and praise and blessingВҰ157913.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ157914 I heardВҰ157951 every creatureВҰ157916 in heavenВҰ157922 and on earth, and under the earth and in the seaВҰ157940вҖ”everything everywhereвҖ”sayingВҰ157952,
\q1 вҖңTo the one sittingВҰ157955 on the throneВҰ157959
\q2 and to the lambВҰ157963,
\q1 be praise and honourВҰ157968 and GLORY and power
\q2 forever and ever.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ157982 the fourВҰ157984 livingВҰ157985 creaturesВҰ157985 said, вҖңMayВҰ157989 itВҰ157989 beВҰ157989 soВҰ157989,вҖқ and the eldersВҰ157994 knelt down and worshipped.
\c 6
\s1 The lamb breaks the first six seals
\rem /s1 The Seven Seals
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ158004 I sawВҰ158005 the lambВҰ158010 breaking the first of the sevenВҰ158014 sealsВҰ158015, andВҰ158016 I heardВҰ158017 one of the fourВҰ158021 livingВҰ158022 creaturesВҰ158022 say, вҖңCome,вҖқ in a thunderousВҰ158029 voiceВҰ158026.
\v 2 SoВҰ158035 I lookedВҰ158036, and wowВҰ158038, there was a whiteВҰ158040 horseВҰ158039 with someone sittingВҰ158043 on it holding a bow \add and arrow\add*. A crownВҰ158053 was givenВҰ158051 to him, and thenВҰ158035 he wentВҰ158055 out as a conqueror to conquer.\x + \xo 6:2: \xt Zech 1:8; 6:3,6.\x*
\v 3 And when \add the lamb\add* broke the second seal, I heardВҰ158070 the second livingВҰ158073 creatureВҰ158073 say, вҖңCome,вҖқ
\v 4 and another horse came out. It was a red horse, and the one sittingВҰ158091 on it was given permission to withdraw peaceВҰ158099 from the earthВҰ158103 so that \add people\add* would slaughter each other, and a large swordВҰ158112 was given to him.\x + \xo 6:4: \xt Zech 1:8; 6:2.\x*
\v 5 ThenВҰ158115 \add the lamb\add* broke the third seal and I heardВҰ158123 the third livingВҰ158126 creatureВҰ158126 say, вҖңCome.вҖқ I lookedВҰ158133, and wowВҰ158135, there was a blackВҰ158137 horseВҰ158136, and the one sittingВҰ158141 on itВҰ158143 held balancing scalesВҰ158146 in hisВҰ158150 handВҰ158149.\x + \xo 6:5: \xt Zech 6:2,6.\x*
\v 6 ThenВҰ158151 I heardВҰ158152 \add somethingВҰ158152\add* like a voiceВҰ158154 from among the fourВҰ158158 livingВҰ158159 creaturesВҰ158159 that said, вҖңA kilo of wheatВҰ158162 for a day's pay, or threeВҰ158165 kilos of barleyВҰ158168 for the same price. ButВҰ158151 don'tВҰ158178 harm the oilВҰ158174 andВҰ158151 wine \add supplies\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 WhenВҰ158180 \add the lamb\add* broke the fourth seal, I heardВҰ158187 the voiceВҰ158188 of the fourth livingВҰ158193 creatureВҰ158193 sayingВҰ158195, вҖңCome.вҖқ
\v 8 ThenВҰ158201 I lookedВҰ158202, and wowВҰ158204, there was a greenВҰ158206 horseВҰ158205. The one sitting on it was named вҖҳDeathВҰ158216вҖҷ, and HadesВҰ158219 was \add sitting\add* behind him. They were givenВҰ158225 authorityВҰ158228 over a quarter of the earth: to execute people with the swordВҰ158237, with famineВҰ158240, with deathВҰ158243, and with the wild animals on the earth.\x + \xo 6:8: \xt Eze 14:21.\x*
\p
\v 9 WhenВҰ158252 \add the lamb\add* broke the fifthВҰ158256 seal, under the altarВҰ158263 I sawВҰ158259 the soulsВҰ158265 of everyone who had been killed because of God's word andВҰ158275 because of the testimonyВҰ158278 thatВҰ158268 theyВҰ158286 had upheld.
\v 10 These souls called out loudlyВҰ158292, вҖңYou, masterВҰ158297, always do what is right and decide what is right! SoВҰ158288 please condemn and punish the people on the earthВҰ158317 who killed us.вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ158318 each of them was givenВҰ158319 a whiteВҰ158326 robeВҰ158324, and told to wait a littleВҰ158338 longer untilВҰ158339 the full number was reached of theirВҰ158348 fellowВҰ158347 servants and brothersВҰ158351 and sistersВҰ158351 who would also be killedВҰ158356 like they were.
\p
\v 12 WhenВҰ158362 \add the lamb\add* broke the sixthВҰ158370 seal, thereВҰ158375 was a violent earthquakeВҰ158373 and the sunВҰ158379 went black like black cloth, and the moonВҰ158388 which was full, went \add red\add* like bloodВҰ158392.\x + \xo 6:12: a \xt Rev 11:13; 16:18; \xo b \xt Isa 13:10; Yoel 2:10,31; 3:15; Mat 24:29; Mrk 13:24-25; Luk 21:25.\x*
\v 13 \add Also\add* the starsВҰ158395 fell out of the skyВҰ158398, just like how a figВҰ158405 treeВҰ158405 out of season drops itsВҰ158411 fruit when itВҰ158411 gets shakenВҰ158419 by a strong windВҰ158415.\x + \xo 6:13-14: \xt Isa 34:4.\x*
\v 14 The sky was split apart like a scrollВҰ158425 beingВҰ158426 rolledВҰ158426 up, and all the mountainsВҰ158430 and islandsВҰ158433 were movedВҰ158439 out of theirВҰ158437 placesВҰ158436.\x + \xo 6:14: \xt Rev 16:20.\x*
\v 15 ThenВҰ158441 the kingsВҰ158443 on the earthВҰ158445, and high-ranking officials, military officers, rich \add people\add* and \add influential individuals\add*, all slavesВҰ158463 and free \add people\add* hid in cavesВҰ158471 and amongВҰ158473 rocksВҰ158475 on the mountainsВҰ158477.\x + \xo 6:15: \xt Isa 2:19,21.\x*
\v 16 They told the mountainsВҰ158481 and rocksВҰ158484, вҖңFall \add down\add* on us and hideВҰ158489 us so that the one sittingВҰ158494 on the throneВҰ158498 can't see us, and \add also\add* from the lamb's angerВҰ158504\x + \xo 6:16: \xt Hos 10:8; Luk 23:30.\x*
\v 17 becauseВҰ158507 today is the terrible dayВҰ158510 when theirВҰ158516 angerВҰ158514 has eventuated, andВҰ158517 who can stand up to that?вҖқ\x + \xo 6:17: \xt Yoel 2:11; Mal 3:2.\x*
\c 7
\s1 The 144,000 marked Israelis
\rem /s1 The 144,000 of Israel Sealed; The 144,000 People of Israel; God's People Will Be Preserved
\p
\v 1 AfterВҰ158522 that I sawВҰ158525 four messengersВҰ158527 standing around the earth, holding \add back\add* the four windsВҰ158538 of the earth so that no windВҰ158546 would blow on land or seaВҰ158553 or on any treeВҰ158559.\x + \xo 7:1: \xt Jer 49:36; Dan 7:2; Zech 6:5.\x*
\v 2 ThenВҰ158561 I sawВҰ158562 anotherВҰ158563 messenger coming up from \add the direction of\add* the risingВҰ158568 sunВҰ158570, and he was holding the livingВҰ158575 God's seal. He called out loudlyВҰ158580 to the fourВҰ158582 messengers that God had permitted to damage the earthВҰ158590 and the seaВҰ158593,
\v 3 sayingВҰ158594, вҖңDon't harm the earthВҰ158600 or the seaВҰ158605 or the treesВҰ158609 untilВҰ158610 weВҰ158613 can \add mark the\add* seal on the foreheadsВҰ158621 of God's servants.вҖқ\x + \xo 7:3: \xt Eze 9:4,6.\x*
\v 4 ThenВҰ158623 I heardВҰ158624 the count of those who were \add marked with\add* the seal. There were 144,000 from all of Yisrael's tribesВҰ158639.
\v 5 There were 12,000 from the tribes of Yehudah, ReubenВҰ158651, GadВҰ158657,
\rem /s1 The Enormous Crowd
\v 6 Asher, Naftali, Menashsheh,
\rem /s1 Praise from the Great Multitude
\v 7 Shimeon (SimeonВҰ158682), LeviВҰ158688, Yissakar (IssacharВҰ158694),
\v 8 Zebulun, Yosef (Joseph), and Benyamin (BenjaminВҰ158713).
\s1 The huge crowd dressed in white
\rem /s1 The Great Multitude in White Robes; The Multitude from Every Nation
\p
\v 9 AfterВҰ158719 thatВҰ158729, I lookedВҰ158721 and wowВҰ158723, there was a hugeВҰ158726 crowdВҰ158724 too large to count, from everyВҰ158736 nationВҰ158737 and tribeВҰ158739 and peopleВҰ158741 and language, standing in front of the throneВҰ158750 and the lambВҰ158754, having been dressed in whiteВҰ158758 robesВҰ158757 and holding palmВҰ158760 branchesВҰ158760,
\v 10 and theyВҰ158767 were shouting loudlyВҰ158770, вҖңOurВҰ158778 \nd GodВҰ158776\nd* who's sittingВҰ158780 on the throneВҰ158784 has saved us! The lambВҰ158791 has saved us!вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ158798 all the messengers stoodВҰ158802 around the throne, and around the eldersВҰ158808 and the four livingВҰ158812 beings. The messengers all knelt down in front of the throne with theirВҰ158822 facesВҰ158820 to the ground and worshipped \nd GodВҰ158826\nd*
\v 12 sayingВҰ158827, вҖңYes, may it be so. May praise and GLORY and wisdomВҰ158836 and thanksВҰ158839 and honourВҰ158842 and powerВҰ158845 and strengthВҰ158848 be \add given\add* to ourВҰ158851 \nd GodВҰ158850\nd* who lives through all the ages! May it be so.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ158858 one of the eldersВҰ158863 asked me, вҖңWho are those people in whiteВҰ158878 robesВҰ158876 andВҰ158858 whereВҰ158882 have they come from?вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңSir, you are the one who knows,вҖқ I answered.\x + \xo 7:14: \xt Dan 12:1; Mat 24:21; Mrk 13:19.\x*
\p And thenВҰ158884 he told me, вҖңThose are the ones who've come through the terrible tribulationВҰ158903, and they've washedВҰ158907 theirВҰ158910 robesВҰ158909 in the bloodВҰ158918 of the lambВҰ158920 and made them whiteВҰ158912.
\v 15 That's why they're here in front of God's throne, and they worship him dayВҰ158932 and nightВҰ158934 in his templeВҰ158937, and the one sittingВҰ158941 on the throne will extend his protection over them.
\v 16 They won't be hungry or thirstyВҰ158956 any longer, and the sunВҰ158965 won't burn them with its scorching heat,\x + \xo 7:16: \xt Isa 49:10.\x*
\v 17 becauseВҰ158970 the lamb that's there at the throneВҰ158977 will shepherdВҰ158978 them. The lamb will guide them to the springsВҰ158988 of living waterВҰ158989, and \nd GodВҰ158993\nd* will \add ensure that\add* everyВҰ158994 tear is wiped away from theirВҰ159000 eyesВҰ158999.вҖқ\x + \xo 7:17: a \xt Psa 23:1; Eze 34:23; \xo b \xt Psa 23:2; Isa 49:10; \xo c \xt Isa 25:8.\x* SHOULD THIS BE IN POETIC FORMAT?
\c 8
\s1 The lamb of seventh seal
\rem /s1 The Seventh Seal and the Golden Censer; The Lamb Breaks the Seventh Seal
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ159001 the lamb broke the seventhВҰ159008 seal andВҰ159001 there was silenceВҰ159010 in heavenВҰ159013 for aboutВҰ159014 half an hourВҰ159015.
\rem /s1 The seven trumpets
\v 2 And I sawВҰ159017 the seven messengersВҰ159020 who stand in front of \nd GodВҰ159024\nd* andВҰ159016 they were each givenВҰ159027 a trumpetВҰ159031.
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ159032 anotherВҰ159033 messengerВҰ159034 cameВҰ159035 andВҰ159032 stoodВҰ159037 at the altar holding a golden bowl for burning incense. He was givenВҰ159050 a lot of incense to offer whichВҰ159067 was to be mingled with the prayersВҰ159058 of all the believers on the golden altar in front of the throneВҰ159070.\x + \xo 8:3: a \xt Amos 9:1; \xo b \xt Exo 30:1,3.\x*
\v 4 SoВҰ159071 the smokeВҰ159075 of the incenseВҰ159077 from the bowl in the messenger'sВҰ159085 handВҰ159083, together with the prayersВҰ159079 of the believers, drifted upwards in front of \nd GodВҰ159088\nd*.
\v 5 ThenВҰ159089 the messengerВҰ159092 took the bowl and filledВҰ159097 it with coals of fireВҰ159102 from the altarВҰ159104, and threw them\f + \fr 8:5 \ft The Greek doesn't specify whether or not the bowl itself was included.\f* onto the earth and that caused peals of thunderВҰ159114 and roaring, and lightningВҰ159120 bolts and an earthquake.\x + \xo 8:5: a \xt Lev 16:12; Eze 10:2; \xo b \xt Exo 19:16; Rev 11:19; 16:18.\x*
\s1 The first four trumpets
\rem /s1 The Seven Trumpets
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ159124 the seven messengersВҰ159127 who had the seven trumpetsВҰ159132, got ready to blow them.
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ159138 the firstВҰ159140 messenger blew his trumpetВҰ159142 and thenВҰ159138 hail and fireВҰ159147 mixedВҰ159148 together with bloodВҰ159151 was thrownВҰ159153 \add down\add* on the earth and a third of the earth was burnt up along with a third of the treesВҰ159167, and all the greenВҰ159172 grassВҰ159171 got burnt up.\x + \xo 8:7: \xt Exo 9:23-25; Eze 38:22.\x*
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ159174 the secondВҰ159176 messengerВҰ159177 blew his trumpetВҰ159178, and somethingВҰ159179 was thrownВҰ159185 into the ocean that was like a hugeВҰ159182, burningВҰ159183 mountainsВҰ159181, and a thirdВҰ159193 of the sea turned into bloodВҰ159196.
\v 9 One third of the living creaturesВҰ159204 in the seaВҰ159208 diedВҰ159198, and a third of the shipsВҰ159217 were destroyed.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ159220 the third messengerВҰ159223 blew his trumpetВҰ159224 and a hugeВҰ159231 starВҰ159230, burning like a torchВҰ159234, fell \add down\add* from the skyВҰ159229 and landed on a third of the riversВҰ159241 and on the springsВҰ159245 of waterВҰ159247.\x + \xo 8:10: \xt Isa 14:12.\x*
\v 11 That starВҰ159252 is named вҖҳBitternessвҖҷ andВҰ159259 a thirdВҰ159263 of those waters turned bitterВҰ159279. Many peopleВҰ159272 died from the waters, becauseВҰ159278 they \add becameВҰ159260 poisonous\add*.\x + \xo 8:11: \xt Jer 9:15.\x*
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ159280 the fourthВҰ159282 messengerВҰ159283 blew his trumpetВҰ159284 and a third of the sun and the moon were struck and the sun didn'tВҰ159312 shine for a third of the dayВҰ159308, nor the moon for a third of the nightВҰ159323. One third of the starsВҰ159300 were struck and went dark.\x + \xo 8:12: \xt Isa 13:10; Eze 32:7; Yoel 2:10,31; 3:15.\x*
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ159325 as I watched, I heardВҰ159328 an eagleВҰ159330 thatВҰ159357 was flyingВҰ159332 high in the sky, shouting loudlyВҰ159337, вҖңThree terrible things will happen to the people who are livingВҰ159344 on the earthВҰ159347 when the threeВҰ159355 remaining messengersВҰ159356 blow their trumpetsВҰ159353.вҖқ
\c 9
