\v 6 SoВҰ161613 it started speaking out anti-God statements, as well as speaking out againstВҰ161622 God's nameВҰ161627 and hisВҰ161628 \add home and\add* those \add who live\add* in heavenВҰ161638.
\v 7 It was given permission to battle against the believers and to conquer them, and itВҰ161655 was given authorityВҰ161656 over everyВҰ161659 tribeВҰ161660 and peopleВҰ161662 and language and nationВҰ161667.\x + \xo 13:7: \xt Dan 7:21.\x*
\v 8 All the people livingВҰ161674 on the earth will worship itвҖ”all of those whose names have never been written in the lamb's book of lifeВҰ161695 since the \add вүҲcreation\add* of the worldвҖ”the lamb who was slaughtered.\f + \fr 13:8 \ft вҖҳsince the creation of the worldвҖҷ is placed to connect with вҖҳwrittenвҖҷ (similar to how it is in 17:8), but the Greek grammar would also allow it to be at the end of the verse (as it is physically in the Greek) connected to вҖҳslaughteredвҖҷ instead (as you'll find in some other translations).\f*\x + \xo 13:8: \xt Psa 69:28.\x*
\p
\v 9 Everyone who wantsВҰ161706 to understandВҰ161706 needsВҰ161708 to listenВҰ161708.
\v 10 If anyone's \add enemies\add* are going to capture them, they will capture them \add and\add* if anyone's \add enemies\add* are going to kill them with a sword, they'll kill them with a sword. So God's people must endureВҰ161735 \add suffering\add* and remain faithfulВҰ161739.\x + \xo 13:10: \xt Jer 15:2; 43:11.\x*
